A: You can dismiss the ProgressDialog in the onConfigurationChanged() method of your activity. This method is called when the device's screen orientation changes.
@Override
public void onConfigurationChanged(Configuration newConfig) {
    super.onConfigurationChanged(newConfig);
    if (progressDialog != null && progressDialog.isShowing()) {
        progressDialog.dismiss();
    }
}

This way, you're ensuring that the ProgressDialog is dismissed when the screen orientation changes, preventing your app from crashing.

A: You can dismiss the ProgressDialog in the onPause() method of your activity. This method is called when your activity is no longer visible to the user.
@Override
protected void onPause() {
    super.onPause();
    if (progressDialog != null && progressDialog.isShowing()) {
        progressDialog.dismiss();
    }
}

This way, you're ensuring that the ProgressDialog is dismissed when your activity is paused, preventing your app from crashing.

